#!/usr/bin/env ruby

require 'optparse'
require 'spec/spec_helper'
require 'mspec/bin/options'

puts <<-EOM
'mspec tag' coming soon

Meanwhile, you can manually add and remove tags from files
in the spec/tags directory. Assume you have a spec at:

  spec/ruby/1.8/core/class/method_spec.rb
  
To exclude a spec from the CI runner, add a line like:

  fails:Class#method does this
  
to the file spec/tags/ruby/1.8/core/class/method_tags.txt
EOM
